  "text": "over Time in Aged Mother Cells. To connect the asymmetric division in young cells to the aging phenotype in old cells, we tracked how these proteins change over time in single mother cells throughout their lifespan, using a recently developed microfluidic device [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . We analyzed Did2p and Tpo3p, which represent a protein involved in endosomal sorting/endosome-to-vacuole transport and a nitrogen source transporter, respectively.",
